          "instruction": "Fill in the blanks to complete the sentences about essential computer hardware components, using the options provided. Refer to the Learning Cards on 'Understanding Computer Hardware Essentials' if needed.",
          "codeTemplate": "The __________, often called the 'brain' of the computer, executes instructions and performs calculations.\n__________ provides fast, temporary storage for data that the CPU is actively using.",
          "options": [
            "CPU",
            "GPU",
            "RAM",
            "HDD"
          ],
          "correctAnswer": "CPU,RAM",
          "explanation": "The CPU (Central Processing Unit) is responsible for executing instructions, and RAM (Random Access Memory) provides fast, temporary storage for active data."
        },
        {
          "instruction": "Complete the following sentences about computer components by dragging the correct terms into the blanks. Use the Flashcards on 'Motherboard' and 'Graphics Card (GPU)' for reference.",
          "codeTemplate": "The __________ is the main circuit board of a computer, connecting all components.\nThe __________ handles the processing and output of images to the display.",
          "options": [
            "Motherboard",
            "Graphics Card (GPU)",
            "Hard Disk Drive (HDD)",
            "CPU"
          ],
          "correctAnswer": "Motherboard,Graphics Card (GPU)",
          "explanation": "The Motherboard connects all components, while the Graphics Card (GPU) processes and outputs images."
        },
        {
          "instruction": "Use the options to fill in the blanks in the sentences below, related to computer hardware. Review the 'Understanding Computer Hardware' Concept Breakdown if you need a reminder.",
          "codeTemplate": "The CPU fetches instructions from __________ and decodes them.\nA __________ is a traditional storage device that uses magnetic platters to store data.",
          "options": [
            "memory",
            "Graphics Card (GPU)",
            "Hard Disk Drive (HDD)",
            "Motherboard"
          ],
          "correctAnswer": "memory,Hard Disk Drive (HDD)",
          "explanation": "The CPU fetches instructions from memory, and a Hard Disk Drive (HDD) is a traditional storage device using magnetic platters."
        }
      ]
